{"cursor":"7883","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\nIn video gaming parlance, an 'achievement', also sometimes known as a 'trophy',\n'badge', 'award', 'stamp', 'medal' or 'challenge', is a meta-goal defined\noutside of a game's parameters. Unlike the systems of quests or levels that\nusually define the goals of a video game and have a direct effect on further\ngameplay, the management of achievements usually takes place outside the\nconfines of the game environment and architecture.\n","linknr":156,"url":"Achievement_(video_gaming)","recorded":1362684071,"links":20,"instances":["psp","software","apple"],"pdf":["http://www.digra.org/dl/db/11307.59151.pdf","http://www.digra.org/dl/db/11307.59151.pdf"],"categories":["Player progress tracking in video games","Video game terminology"],"headings":["Purpose and motivation","Implementations","See also","References"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["steam","software"],["littlebigplanet","psp"],["ios","apple"],["steam","software"]],"members":["littlebigplanet","steam","ios"],"related":["Video_gaming","Power-ups","Online_game","First-person_shooters","Gamertag","Live_Anywhere","Xbox_360","Games_for_Windows_-_Live","PlayStation_Network","World_of_Warcraft","Sony_Computer_Entertainment","Valve_Software","PlayStation_3","Steam_(software)","Nintendo","Wii","Nintendo_DS","PlayStation_Portable","Modnation_Racers","Pinball_Heroes","LittleBigPlanet_(PSP)","PlayStation_Vita","Microsoft","Windows_Phone_7","Xbox_Live","Apple_Inc.","Game_Center","IOS_(Apple)","IPhone","IPad","IPod_touch","Kongregate","Adobe_Flash","Xbox_360","Xbox_Live","PlayStation_Network","Steam_(software)"]}